<h1>Problem 1854 - 2011 All-Russian MO Grade 11, P8 of 8, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Let \(N\) be the midpoint of arc \(ABC\), of a triangle \(ABC\), let \(M\) be the midpoint of \(AC\) and let \(I_1, I_2\) be the incentres of triangles \(ABM\) and \(CBM\). Prove that the points \(I_1, I_2, B, N\) lie on a circle.</p>
